article.description: A'Dia Mathies scored 27 points and Victoria Dunlap added 22 points and 11 rebounds to help Kentucky (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) beat Arkansas 71-57 on Sunday for its seventh straight win.
article.headline: Dunlaps keys second-half rally as UK moves half game behind Tennessee
article.linkText: Win moves No. 18 UK half game from SEC lead
article.story:
FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. -- A'Dia Mathies scored 27 points and Victoria Dunlap added 22 points and 11 rebounds to help Kentucky (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) beat Arkansas 71-57 on Sunday for its seventh straight win.

Dunlap scored 20 of her points in the second half as Kentucky (20-3, 8-2 Southeastern Conference) broke a 33-33 halftime tie. The Wildcats moved within a half-game of idle Tennessee for the conference lead.

Lyndsay Harris scored 20 points and Charity Ford added 10 to lead Arkansas (9-14, 1-9). The Razorbacks led 8-0 and Harris hit four 3-pointers in the first half to help Arkansas stay close with the Wildcats.
